@node 5 "Versions...just some!"

V1.0:   01.April`95 - Never been released... just a working beta
                      Based upon a bad programmed AREXX-Script I downloaded
                      once somewhere...
                    - It`s no APRILSCHERZ!

V2.0:   15.April`95 - Never been released too...
                    - Added error-handling
                    - Added advanced stripping of bad chars
                    - Added editing option

V3.0:   25.April`95 - meanwhile ©ommodore was sold to Escom ;-)
                    - First Release!
                    - Added Multifileselection
                    - Added requesters
                    - Added DizZMagIc-Script for non-interactive use!

V3.1:   27.April`95 - Fixed problem with Directoy scans!
                      Errorhandling:Now a requester opens when you try
                      to scan a whole directory!
                    - Fixed a problem with locale-handling
                    - Highered the limit of chars from 70 to 79
                    - Advanced stripping of bad chars again
                    - Added the function to scroll after entrys

V3.2:   28.April`95 - Added the function to break during work
                      (press both mousebuttons to BREAK!)
                    - Cleared code a bit
                    - Fixed the handling bug! Now I use the original
                      CLI-command FILENOTE for inserting the comments
                      in your files. The internal dOPUS-command made
                      some problems in handling files l8er...
                    - Removed DizZMagIc from archive!
                      Now the INTERACTIVE & NONINTERACTIVE version
                      are the same...
                      When starting the script you can give the
                      argument INTERACTIVE and from then on
                      the comment-editor will come up all the time!

V3.3    29.April`95 - Added File_ID.DIZ to REXX-Script
                    - Now BREAKS are recognized faster!
                    - Indicator in the Status-Line added (now you
                      can see how many files are left and which file
                      is in work.)
                    - some internal changes in the code!

V3.4    11.May  `95 - 3.3 was not really a FINAL-release though!
                      I got some new ideas...
                    - NEW OPTION: NODIZED
                      Added DIZ-Ed V2.1 support
                      If the checked file doesn`t have
                      a FILE_ID.DIZ your are asked to paint one
                      with DIZ-Ed. DIZ-Ed will then be loaded...
                      Just works in INTERACTIVE mode!
                      To switch this function off give the argument
                      "NODIZED" after the "INTERACTIVE" option!
                    - If you want to have DIZ-Ed on dOPUS-screen then
                      go to its PREFERENCES screen and enter the 
                      SCREEN -> FRONTMOST mode!
                    - NEW OPTION: MAKELIST
                      When starting with "ComDizZ MAKELIST"
                      a sorted file will be created with name
                      and comment in a row in your actual dir!
                      This is useful for people who want to spread
                      lists of their Up/Download dirs to friends
                      who should know what is in the archives!
                    - Improved Errorhandling:
                      Filenames that include ILLEGAL Chars (such as *,=)
                      will not be handled. You have to rename such
                      files and try again l8er, but you`ll be informed!

V3.5    21.May  `95 - Found a bug in handling filenames with SAPCES!
                      ->fixed
                    - the abort function is enhanced
                    - Found a bug in the executable of SNATCHDIZ by
                      Rascal/Supreme. The exe didn`t work on 040!
                      Result of using a bad cruncher but now fixed
                      because the exe is now uncrunched here in the
                      archive! Please copy it over your last exe
                      that came with the laster releases!
                        
V3.6    16.June `95 - How drunk was I? I came back from NEXUS7 (sux!)
                      and started the release of 3.5... but look above ^
                      There are many mispelled and totally wrong 
                      things being told in the 3.5 release...
                      I must have been brainstuck!
                    - Files with spaces weren`t handled correctly
                      in 3.5! SnatchDiz has an error. Now a requester
                      will popup to inform you that you have to rename
                      the files!
                    - optimized the code (espacially the loops!)
                      now it`s a little faster...
                    - found a bug in localization! When not using ENGLISH-
                      catalog the ERROR-requester was faulty!
                      Should work now!
                    - Yep Gandalf... I haven`t found any solution for YOUR
                      problem yet... probably the error is gone now ?!


V3.7    21.June `95 - Now ComDizZ works with more then one DOPUS-Rexx-Port,
                      so multitasking is is now enabled! :-)
                    - Added a simple "beep on error" !
                    - Added a little infowindow that shows up while
                      working (grin!)
                    - due to the optimizing it is slightly faster again!
                    - now after editing the fileid with DizEd ComDizZ will
                      request for editing the comment. You don`t have 
                      to start the script again on the edited file!
                    - thisone seems to be the last version...
                      if you want something in here or I see bugreports
                      i`ll bring out a 4.0 with new features!

V3.8    19.July `95 - all people that installed the BETA should install
                      ALL files AGAIN !!!
                    - Never thought there would be a NEXT release! ^^^
                    - Update of SnatchDiz 2.2 ©`95 rascAL/shooT is
                      distributed in the package!
                      Because of that ComDizZ handles files with SPACES!
                               yep... that took a long time :-)
                    - Now ComDizZ is much faster !!! Snatchdiz 2.2`s new
                      feature is that you can make it resident!
                      Copy the new Version to your C:
                      DELETE, FILENOTE, SNATCHDIZ - All this files HAVE
                                                    to be in C: path 
                                                    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                      Thanx go out to rascAL/shooT for the idea,
                           that should have come to my mind before!
                      ----------------------------------------------------
                       A little comparison of 3.7->3.8 speed enhancement,
                       tested speed with 16 Textfiles in 187248 bytes:

                       V3.7    ¦->¦   V3.8 ¦  all on orig (c)2620-68020
                       --------¦->¦--------¦  may differ on your machine.
                       53.64sec¦->¦36.10sec¦  that`s speeeed-improvement!
                      ----------------------------------------------------
                    - Now in INTERACTIVE mode you can EDIT more then
                      80 chars! But remember that only the first 80
                      will be written to the filecomment!
                    - Advanced stripping of bad chars again
                    - Statusline is repaired to show allways the right
                      file at the right time!
                    - Won`t do a Dopus5 Version yet... nobody seems to be
                      interested in this tool, cause of no replys...
                      Now start to mail me sucker... I wanna know who
                      uses this bigshit! ;-)


V3.9    06.August`95- Some incredible NEW enhancements: Thanx to Gandalf/PHN
                      for the ideas!
                      If you are downloading new files and you want to
                      ComDizZ`em immediatly you HAD the problem, that you
                      probably don`t know which files were NEW!
                      But now you can choose the new option DATECHECK!
                      DATECHECK will remember the last time you used ComDizZ
                      (files !CDlDIR will be created in your path)
                      and will then automatically SELECT the latest files and
                      progress them! You need the file DATE in a path!
                      (edit the preferences... see last updatepoint!)
                      The first time you start this option all files
                      in the chosen dir will be selected (files >01.01.1978!)
                      By the way, I never had this problem Gandalf had, because
                      I use one window that is sorted by time, so I can see
                      which files are new... Nobody needs that anymore :-)
                      By the way... does anybody need this REXX-Script ????
                      Nobody (except Gandalf) gave me a feedback... and not a
                      feet in my back!
                      Now it`s Saturday morning 05:03 and I start to feel
                      a little tired though...
                    - A yap, I forgot to say that another bug is fixed.
                      The CR`s in the File_ID.Diz weren`t converted correctly
                      that sometimes 2 words wouldn`t have a space in between
                      them... This is gone and everything is readable now!
                    - Fixed a bug... NODIZED didn`t work well but will now!
                    - Preferences ADDED! Just load the script in an editor
                      and edit the PREFERENCES part to your system needs!
                      

Future enhancement: 

Is there something you want in here???
Just search for a contacting address !!!
@endnode
